description.narrative: (Tanzania): This project has two objectives: execute evidence-based, coordinated social and behavior change communication initiatives, including to increase use of family planning, among others; and reinforce systems for coordinating and delivering social and behavior change communication. The project seeks to coordinate social and behavior change communication at the national, regional, district and community levels. The geographic focus is 13 regions: Mara, Mwanza, Shinyanga, Geita, Kigoma, Kagera, Simiyu, Rukwa, Katavi, Mtwara, Lindi, Ruvuma and Tabora. FY 2014 funds will target HIV prevention, family planning and reproductive health, malaria and maternal and child health, including zinc and EPI. The U.S. Government will support the implementation of a national, multi-channeled family planning campaign that reflects best practices in behavior change and promotion of prevention and healthy timing and spacing of pregnancies and a safe motherhood campaign, including radio, print materials, community outreach activities and an SMS platform. The platform will be supported by a radio distance learning program and community mobilization with health and economic development resource people.
